pen Divide]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>拜登总统的命令是在中国经济放缓、新冠疫情封锁以及两国之间紧张关系加剧的背景下发布的<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001123931"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833088?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">财政部长珍妮特·耶伦上个月访问北京时试图缓解中国对当时正在讨论的投资限制的担忧。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：POOL/来自路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001123931"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/charles-hutzler" itemprop="url" rel="author">查尔斯·赫茨勒</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 10 日上午 12:28 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-and-china-poised-to-drift-further-apart-after-investment-ban-1e37427d"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>华盛顿——经过多年将中国企业列入黑名单并审查它们在美国的投资，拜登政府<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-to-ban-some-investments-in-china-71f519d6?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">正在向美国企业发出明确的信号</a>，要求其将投资从中国转移出去。</p><p>拜登总统周三发布的一项行政命令虽然狭隘地针对具有军事、监视和网络能力的关键前沿技术，但更广泛的目标是重新安排美国资本和专业知识从其<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-allies-could-counter-chinas-economic-coercionif-they-unite-c45d2f8d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">最大的全球竞争对手的</a>流动。</p><p>该命令禁止美国投资<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-u-s-uses-supply-chain-sway-to-throttle-chinas-chip-development-11666526403?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">先进半导体</a>和量子计算，并要求美国投资者就其他类型半导体和人工智能的投资通知华盛顿。 It also bars US citizens and permanent residents from taking part in prohibited deals.</p><p>白宫官员表示，该命令旨在剥夺中国获得美国风险投资和私募股权公司投资带来的技术诀窍、市场准入和其他好处。除了中国<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-slips-into-deflation-in-warning-sign-for-world-economy-bbefb179" target="_blank" class="icon none">经济增长疲软</a>、新冠疫情封锁导致前往中国变得困难，以及最近在华盛顿和北京之间紧张局势加剧之际，针对美国和其他外国公司的施压行动，这可能会进一步扰乱在中国开展业务的美国公司。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833086?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">拜登总统的命令针对的是具有军事、监视和网络能力的关键前沿技术。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：乔纳森·恩斯特/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>Andrew Polk, a partner with the boutique research firm Trivium China, said that while US companies he advises remain interested in China&#39;s market, many have grown hesitant.</p><p> “我们总是说——这引起了我们客户的共鸣——中国的风险调整回报已经发生了巨大变化，”波尔克说。 “所以我们看到很多公司从根本上重新思考他们的中国战略。这并不意味着他们一定会改变它们，但他们现在正在对它们进行压力测试，因为我们显然处于一个新环境中。”</p><p>周三的命令是在华盛顿和北京在台湾、乌克兰战争、间谍活动和技术控制等问题上经历了数月的严重紧张关系之后，正处于脆弱的关系之中。官员和安全专家表示，短期内，近几个月<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/janet-yellen-says-u-s-china-making-progress-on-managing-economic-tensions-1e2c07?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">脆弱的外交进展</a>可能会持续下去。</p><p>中国领导人习近平认为，在经济陷入通货紧缩<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sputtering-trade-fuels-fears-for-a-connected-world-81c99922?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">、增长放缓和外国投资大幅下降之际，</a>与美国关系的平静（至少是暂时的）可以提升他在国内的威望。中国外交部高级官员杨涛上周在华盛顿与国务院和其他官员进行了讨论，重点是为习近平出席11月在旧金山举行的亚太领导人峰会以及与拜登举行单独会谈做准备据了解讨论情况的人士透露。</p><p>官员们表示，双方还推动修复沟通渠道，本月初步同意成立工作组来讨论亚太地区和海事问题。目前仍在讨论商务部长吉娜·雷蒙多（Gina Raimondo）是否可能在本月晚些时候访问北京，这将是拜登政府高级官员自 6 月以来第四次访问北京。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=607DAEAC-FDF3-4309-B753-4A08C846B405&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fu-s-and-china-poised-to-drift-further-apart-after-investment-ban-1e37427d&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">从喷气式飞机到电动汽车再到超级计算机，《华尔街日报》与不同的行业和技术专家讨论了两国在设计、工程和战略方面的匹配情况。照片插图：迈克尔·塔布和盖蒂图片社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>然而，从长远来看，美国和中国陷入竞争，迫使两国割裂数十年来稳定两国关系的经济和商业联系，而新的投资限制可能会加速两国进一步分裂的势头。</p><p> “关于多元化、去风险、脱钩、解开的言论——选择你的‘D字’，无论你喜欢哪个——它确实已经深入华盛顿的头脑，越来越多地在硅谷，而且这确实是在华尔街传播的前国家安全委员会官员丽莎·托宾 (Liza Tobin) 表示，她目前在华盛顿的一个专门研究技术政策的组织“特别竞争研究项目”工作。</p><p>曾经大力涌入中国的风险投资公司已经退出，部分原因是紧张局势加剧； Crunchbase 的数据显示，从 2021 年到 2022 年，美国对中国初创企业的投资下降了 30% 以上，今年还将进一步下降。</p><p>例如，据一位知情人士透露，总部位于加利福尼亚州的风险投资公司 Lightspeed Venture Partners 于 2006 年成立了中国分部，由于风险原因，该公司已削减了对中国初创企业的投资。</p><p>保卫民主基金会研究员、供应链情报公司 Horizo​​n Advisory 联合创始人内特·皮卡西克 (Nate Picarsic) 表示，“这一举措传达的真正信息是，这是一条持久的轨迹”，公司和投资者必须考虑这一点。 “地缘政治和国家安全风险已成为永久性的问题。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833087?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">随着中国从疫情中恢复过来，今年的经济增长出现了放缓。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：TINGSHU WANG/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>随着近几个月行政命令的形成，中国官员敦促美国不要通过该命令，并指责华盛顿试图阻碍中国的发展。该命令周三公布后，中国驻华盛顿大使馆表达了北京方面的失望，并表示美国正在将贸易武器化，并在维护经济关系的声明上出尔反尔。</p><p> “美方一再表示无意与中国‘脱钩’，但实际上却一再与中国‘脱钩、切断供应链’，”美国大使馆发言人刘鹏宇在一份声明中表示。 “它不断升级对中国的打压和限制。”</p><p>过去十年中，在习近平政府制定了主导尖端行业的计划，并加大了对外国公司转让专有技术的压力后，有关技术和市场准入的争端已酝酿多年，并在过去十年中爆发为更加激烈的冲突。</p><p>特朗普政府将中国军方供应商列入黑名单并加强对中国在美投资的审查，随后拜登政府又全面禁止先进半导体及其制造设备的转让以及美国公民和永久居民的参与在那个部门。美国还让盟友日本和荷兰效仿。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/beijing-bans-micron-as-supplier-to-big-chinese-firms-citing-national-security-5f326b90?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">中国进行了报复</a>，对对绿色技术至关重要的矿物出口实施管制，并禁止美国芯片制造商<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/MU" class="company-name">美光科技</a>在关键基础设施中使用产品。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>您认为中美关系将走向何方？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>财政部长珍妮特·耶伦上个月访问北京时试图缓解中国对当时正在讨论的投资限制的担忧，并阻止报复。她说，她解释说，这些措施的目的是缩小范围，是为了国家安全目的，而不是为了经济优势，她预计北京也会这样做。</p><p> “国家安全是我们不能妥协的事情，我们会保护它，即使这会损害我们自己狭隘的经济利益，我们也会这样做。但当我们采取这些确实对中国经济产生影响的行动时，我们将确保这些行动是透明的、目标明确的、解释清楚的，”耶伦上个月在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/PARA" class="">哥伦比亚广播</a><span class="company-name-type">公司的</span>“面对国家”节目中表示。 ”</p><p> “我要指出的是，中国也通过出口管制和其他类似手段保护自己的国家安全，”耶伦说。</p><p>尽管中国大使馆周三的声明并未暗示进行报复，但中国官员表示，鉴于习近平优先考虑维护中国利益，北京可能会采取报复行动。如果北京这样做，它可能会谨慎选择，以避免伤害本国企业并进一步削弱经济。</p><p>其中一个特别的弱点是电动汽车和太阳能技术，中国在这两个领域的供应链中占据主导地位。保卫民主基金会的皮卡西克表示，他认为投资限制会蔓延开来，影响美国投资者进入其他领域的意愿，特别是生物技术等可以增强军事或警察能力的领域。</p><p> “The structural fundamentals here are ones of competition and escalation, and I don&#39;t think there&#39;s anything that we&#39;ve seen so far—from the US government signaling around this move, Chinese expectations and potential reactions—that would suggest any break from that,” he said.</p><p class="articleTagLine"> —Berber Jin、Lingling Wei 和 Vivian Salama 对本文做出了贡献。</p><p>写信给查尔斯·赫兹勒 (Charles Hutzler)： <a href="mailto:charles.hutzler@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">charles.hutzler@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 04:28:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-and-china-poished-to-drift-further-apart-after-investment-ban-1e37427d</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-and-china-poished-to-drift-further-apart-after-investment-ban-1e37427d<author><![CDATA[Charles Hutzler]]></author><category>华尔街日报华盛顿</category><category>华尔街日报</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>经济表现/指标</category><category>经济增长/衰退</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>呼吸道疾病</category><category>国际关系</category><category>健康</category><category>医疗条件</category><category>疫情/流行病</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>新型冠状病毒</category><category>传染性疾病</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>经济表现</category><category>指标</category><category>经济增长</category><category>经济衰退</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>呼吸道疾病</category><category>国际关系</category><category>健康</category><category>医疗条件</category><category>爆发</category><category>流行病</category><category>政治</category><category>国内政治</category><category>新型冠状病毒</category><category>传染性疾病</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[U.S. Ally Promised to Send Aid to Sudan. It Sent Weapons Instead.]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>阿联酋的武器运输正在助长一场已造成 3,900 多人死亡的战争，这与拜登政府结束冲突的努力背道而驰<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831056/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="自四月中旬以来，苏丹的战争已造成数千人丧生，并使该国陷入人道主义灾难。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>自四月中旬以来，苏丹的战争已造成数千人丧生，并使该国陷入人道主义灾难。纵梁/Shutterstock<span>纵梁/Shutterstock</span> </figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001119615"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001119615"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/nicholas-bariyo" itemprop="url" rel="author">尼古拉斯·巴里约 (Nicholas Bariyo)</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/benoit-faucon" itemprop="url" rel="author">伯努瓦·福孔 (Benoit Faucon)</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 10 日上午 12:02（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/a-u-s-ally-promised-to-send-aid-to-sudan-it-sent-weapons-instead-82d396f"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>乌干达恩德培——六月初，当一架货机降落在乌干达最繁忙的机场时，其飞行文件显示，这架货机载有阿拉伯联合酋长国为苏丹难民提供的人道主义援助物资。</p><p>乌干达官员表示，他们在飞机货舱中发现了数十个绿色塑料箱，里面装满了弹药、突击步枪和其他小型武器，而不是飞机舱单上列出的食品和医疗用品。</p><p> 6 月 2 日在恩德培机场发现的武器是美国盟友阿联酋支持苏丹军阀穆罕默德·哈姆丹·达加洛中将的努力的一部分，后者正在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sudan-khartoum-military-what-is-happening-447d40e2?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">争夺非洲第三大国的控制权。</a>官员表示。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="462" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831053?width=700&amp;height=462" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Lt. Gen. Mohamed Hamdan Dagalo is a warlord battling Sudan&#39;s military for control of Africa&#39;s third-largest country.</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：MOHAMED NURELDIN ABDALLAH/REUTERS</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>据非营利性武装冲突地点和事件数据项目称，官员们表示，阿联酋的秘密武器运输正在助长一场战争，自<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sudan-rivalry-between-powerful-generals-erupts-in-warfare-3fdf7452?&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">4 月 15 日战争爆发</a>以来，这场战争已<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-and-other-diplomats-in-sudan-are-attacked-as-violence-flares-6211c1ae?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">使苏丹陷入人道主义灾难</a>，并造成 3,900 多人死亡。武装达加洛的快速支援部队民兵可能会加剧阿联酋和美国之间的摩擦，而美国一直在努力调解结束战争。</p><p>联合国机构和人权组织指责快速支援部队民兵在苏丹侵犯人权，包括杀害平民。</p><p>阿联酋政府在回答《华尔街日报》的提问时表示，它支持和平解决苏丹冲突，并“寻求提供一切形式的支持，以减轻人道主义苦难”。该公司表示，已向受战争影响的人们运送了约 2000 吨人道主义援助物资，包括食品和医疗用品，并在邻国乍得建立了一家野战医院。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831078?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">今年早些时候，阿联酋驻苏丹大使哈马德·穆罕默德·阿尔尼比在苏丹港机场向运送援助物资的飞机机组人员致意。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：穆罕默德·阿里·哈里西/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>无国界医生组织发言人表示，该组织没有从阿联酋获得武器或其他军事物资，并否认其武装分子参与了侵犯人权的行为。</p><p>阿联酋可能押注于达加洛，以帮助保护阿联酋<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/stakes-in-sudans-war-include-russian-gold-nile-dam-key-shipping-lane-e49c0b8?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在苏丹的利益</a>，因为苏丹位于红海、通往尼罗河的战略位置和巨大的黄金储备。阿联酋的利益包括大片苏丹农田和计划耗资 60 亿美元的红海港口的股份。</p><p>联合国监察员此前<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-a-e-boosted-arms-transfers-tolibyato-salvage-warlords-campaign-u-n-panel-finds-11601412059?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">指责阿布扎比向哈利法·哈夫塔尔运送武器</a>，包括无人机、激光制导炸弹和装甲车，</p>苏丹西北部邻国利比亚的一名民兵指挥官。哈夫塔尔和达加洛都曾与俄罗斯瓦格纳集团合作，允许该准军事组织进入<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russian-oil-grab-in-libya-fuels-u-s-kremlin-tensions-in-mideast-11595772000?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">利比亚的油田</a>和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/who-will-control-wagners-empire-of-war-and-gold-22444d60?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">苏丹的金矿</a>。<p></p><p>据联合国称，达加洛的无国界医生组织和苏丹武装部队之间的战斗已导致超过 400 万人离开家园，而约 2400 万人（约占该国人口的一半） <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/cut-off-from-food-and-cash-sudanese-starve-as-fighting-drags-on-eaea355f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">现在需要食物</a>和其他人道主义援助。超过30万名难民逃离无国界医生组织在达尔富尔的据点，越过边境进入乍得。 6 月 2 日航班的舱单将这些货物列为对难民的人道主义援助。</p><p>据包括人权观察在内的当地和国际人权组织称，自四月以来，无国界医生组织战士和当地民兵联盟袭击了城镇和村庄，强奸妇女并杀害了数百名平民。继 7 月发现数个乱葬坑后，国际刑事法院检察官表示，他正在调查达尔富尔地区潜在的新战争罪行，达尔富尔是 2000 年代初期种族灭绝的发生地。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831076?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">苏丹首都喀土穆五月的战斗结束后，浓烟升起。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="729" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832077?width=1260&amp;height=729" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">本月早些时候，逃离冲突的苏丹人越过边境进入乍得。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：ZOHRA BENSEMRA/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>自 5 月以来，美国官员与沙特阿拉伯官员一道推动了吉达和谈，但由于无国界医生组织和军方多次违反停火协议，正式谈判于 6 月暂停。</p><p>美国国务院发言人表示：“我们会对有关冲突双方获得任何外部支持的报道感到担忧。” “我们继续与阿联酋和其他一些合作伙伴接触和协调，努力敦促苏丹停止敌对行动和人道主义援助准入。”</p><p>熟悉拜登政府非洲政策的人士表示，华盛顿知道阿联酋向无国界部队运送武器，并已向阿布扎比当局表达了其担忧。</p><p>在 6 月 2 日航班上发现武器和弹药的乌干达官员表示，这架阿联酋飞机被允许继续飞往乍得东部的阿姆贾拉斯国际机场。随后，乌干达官员表示，他们接到上级命令，停止检查从阿联酋经停的航班。最近几周，又增加了数十架航班。</p><p> “我们不被允许再检查这些飞机。他们现在是国防部的责任，”一位官员说。 “我们被警告不要拍照。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831734?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">阿联酋政府表示，已向苏丹运送了约2000吨人道主义援助物资，包括食品和医疗用品。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：穆罕默德·阿里·哈里西/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>乌干达国防部发言人表示，恩德培机场负责大量货运航班，但否认有任何飞机使用该机场经乍得向无国界医生组织供应武器。</p><p>在最新的一次交付中，卡车满载军用物资<strong>&nbsp;</strong>这位非洲官员和一名前美国官员表示，7 月最后一周，来自阿联酋的一架飞机离开阿姆贾拉斯机场前往苏丹扎尔克地区，那里是无国界武装力量在达尔富尔北部的一个据点。</p><p>阿联酋的武器交付也引发了人们对乍得政府忠诚度的质疑。美国和法国将乍得总统穆罕默德·代比<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/washingtons-dilemma-in-chad-defense-or-democracy-45b40573?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">视为打击圣战武装分子和俄罗斯在该地区扩张的盟友</a>。</p><p>今年早些时候，美国官员<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-intelligence-points-to-wagner-plot-against-key-western-ally-in-africa-29867547?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">警告代比</a>，瓦格纳老板叶夫根尼·普里戈任正在与乍得叛军合作，破坏其政府的稳定，并可能杀死他。</p><p>然而，熟悉拜登政府政策的人士表示，阿联酋向达加洛运送武器是为了支持瓦格纳在非洲最亲密的合作伙伴之一。乍得信息部长阿齐兹·穆罕默德·萨利赫没有回应置评请求。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831069?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">熟悉拜登政府政策的人士表示，阿联酋向穆罕默德·哈姆丹·达加洛的快速支援部队民兵运送武器是为了支持瓦格纳集团在非洲最亲密的合作伙伴之一。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Mahmoud Hjaj/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831737?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">在六月的一次会议上，阿联酋总统谢赫·穆罕默德·本·扎耶德·阿勒纳哈扬（右）与乍得总统穆罕默德·代比（左）签署了军事、采矿和能源协议。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：hassan al menhali/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>阿联酋总统谢赫·穆罕默德·本·扎耶德·阿勒纳哈扬于 6 月 14 日在阿布扎比会见了代比，两位领导人在那里签署了一系列有价值的军事、采矿和能源协议。乌干达官员表示，会议结束后不久，经恩德培飞往乍得的航班变得更加频繁。</p><p>写信给 Nicholas Bariyo <a href="mailto:nicholas.bariyo@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">（nicholas.bariyo@wsj.com）</a>和 Benoit Faucon（ <a href="mailto:benoit.faucon@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">benoit.faucon@wsj.com</a> ）</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 04:02:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/aus-ally-promised-to-send-aid-to-sudan-it-sent-weapons-instead-82d396f</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/aus-ally-promised-to-send-aid-to-sudan-it-sent-weapons-instead-82d396f<author><![CDATA[Nicholas BariyoBenoit Faucon]]></author><category>专有的</category><category>货运/物流</category><category>运输/物流</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>发展/人道主义援助</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>穆罕默德·哈姆丹·达加洛</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>发展</category><category>人道主义援助</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>货运</category><category>后勤</category><category>运输</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ecuadorean Presidential Candidate Assassinated]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>费尔南多·比亚维森西奥 (Fernando Villavicencio) 在谴责贩毒团伙和腐败后，对他收到的威胁置之不理<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001123803"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=3A297452-49E9-4885-AD64-0A664604940D&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fecuador-presidential-candidate-who-had-denounced-gangs-is-assassinated-dad61aa5&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Ecuadorean Presidential Candidate Fernando Villavicencio was shot dead as he left a campaign event in Quito, less than two weeks before the election. He was a sharp critic of corruption and said he had received threats from a local gang. Photo: Shutterstock<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001123803"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/ryan-dube" itemprop="url" rel="author">瑞安·杜贝</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/juan-forero" itemprop="url" rel="author">胡安·福雷罗</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 9 日晚上 10:11（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ecuador-presidential-candidate-who-had-denounced-gangs-is-assassinated-dad61aa5"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>厄瓜多尔总统吉列尔莫·拉索表示，厄瓜多尔总统候选人费尔南多·比亚维森西奥周三被枪杀，距离该国选举不到两周。该<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/cocaine-trade-and-gang-violence-strike-hard-in-once-peaceful-ecuador-bad953c8?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">国暴力犯罪激增</a>。</p><p> 59 岁的前记者兼国会议员比亚维森西奥 (Villavicencio) 在首都基多一所学校参加竞选活动后被杀。</p><p> “对总统候选人费尔南多·维拉维森西奥被暗杀感到愤怒和沮丧，”拉索在 X（该网站以前称为 Twitter）上写道。 “为了纪念他并为了他的斗争，我向你们保证，这一罪行将不会逍遥法外。”</p><p>总检察长办公室称，一名杀人嫌疑人被捕后因伤重死亡。</p><p>网上发布的一段视频显示，比亚维森西奥上车后不久，人们纷纷倒地，枪声响起。比亚维森西奥的朋友、记者克里斯蒂安·苏里塔发布的另一段视频显示，人们尖叫着，挤在学校的地板上。</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> “他们杀了我的朋友，”祖里塔在发布视频后不久发推文。</p><p>比亚维森西奥严厉批评腐败和贩毒团伙，这些团伙最近在这个曾经相对和平的国家制造了流血事件。他最近表示，他收到了当地一个名为 Choneros 的帮派的威胁。该团伙与墨西哥锡那罗亚贩毒集团有联系，安全专家表示，该集团确保<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/colombias-acreage-of-coca-used-to-make-cocaine-surges-to-record-11666306614?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">来自哥伦比亚的可卡因运输经过厄瓜多尔</a>，然后向北运往美国</p><p>“这证实了我们的竞选提案将严重影响这些犯罪结构，”他在谈到最近的威胁时说道。 “我不害怕。”</p><p>比亚维森西奥在另一场谈到经济的演讲中表示，“谈论投资需要拆除犯罪结构。”</p><p> “我们的犯罪经济由贩毒、非法采矿和……公共部门腐败贿赂提供资金，”他说。</p><p>拉索呼吁举行新的选举以<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ecuador-president-dissolves-congress-ahead-of-impeachment-vote-987f5883?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">避免遭到国会弹劾</a>，厄瓜多尔人定于 8 月 20 日投票选出新总统。政治分析人士表示，比亚维森西奥是有机会在第一轮投票中获得第二名的候选人之一。民意调查显示，没有人可能获得足够的票数在第一轮中彻底赢得总统职位。这种情况需要在排名前两位的候选人之间进行第二轮决选。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833069?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">周三晚上，厄瓜多尔总统候选人费尔南多·比亚维森西奥在基多举行集会后被枪杀，人们纷纷躲藏起来。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>比亚维森西奥的去世引起了人们的哀悼。</p><p> “作为一名厄瓜多尔人，我对费尔南多·比亚维森西奥被犯罪分子暗杀深感悲痛，”另一位总统候选人扬·托皮克(Jan Topic)在网上发布的视频中说道。 “今天比以往任何时候都更需要铁拳。”</p><p>作为一名记者，比亚维森西奥领导了大量调查并撰写了有关政府腐败的书籍，特别是在前总统执政期间</p>拉斐尔·科雷亚 (Rafael Correa) 于 2020 年因腐败缺席被定罪。<p></p><p>比亚维森西奥后来当选为国会议员并领导监督委员会，负责调查腐败行为。他严厉批评<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-global-mega-projects-infrastructure-falling-apart-11674166180?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">中国向厄瓜多尔提供的贷款</a>，包括大型水电项目的贷款。</p><p> “厄瓜多尔受到了伤害，”他去年在国会办公室接受采访时告诉《华尔街日报》。</p><p>厄瓜多尔曾经是拉丁美洲最安全的国家之一，现在已成为<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/inside-the-experiment-to-stop-the-carnage-in-latin-america-11546275481?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">最危险的国家之一</a>。警方和安全专家表示， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/colombias-acreage-of-coca-used-to-make-cocaine-surges-to-record-11666306614?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">邻国哥伦比亚创纪录的可卡因产量</a>以及墨西哥和阿尔巴尼亚贩毒集团支持的厄瓜多尔贩毒团伙之间的暴力事件引发了暴力浪潮。</p><p>据内政部称，自 2019 年以来，凶杀案增加了四倍，去年达到创纪录的 4,800 起，并<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/andes-turmoil-rattles-governments-spurs-migration-to-u-s-d8396753?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">导致移民激增</a>，主要是前往美国。自 2020 年以来，暴力事件大幅增加，主要发生在沿海城市瓜亚基尔，犯罪团伙争夺通往海港的可卡因贩运路线的控制权。警方和居民称，暗杀者枪杀检察官和警察，将尸体吊在桥上，并招募儿童。</p><p>写信给 Ryan Dubé（ <a href="mailto:ryan.dube@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">ryan.dube@wsj.com）</a>和 Juan Forero（ <a href="mailto:juan.forero@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">juan.forero@wsj.com）</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 02:11:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ecuador-presidential-candidate-who-had-denounced-gangs-is-assassination-dad61aa5</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ecuador-presidential-candidate-who-had-denounced-gangs-is-assassination-dad61aa5<author><![CDATA[Ryan DubéJuan Forero]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>腐败</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>毒品贩运/交易</category><category>金融犯罪</category><category>帮派</category><category>凶杀案</category><category>犯罪企业</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>贩运/走私</category><category>选举</category><category>国家/总统选举</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>腐败</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>贩毒</category><category>交易</category><category>金融犯罪</category><category>帮派</category><category>凶杀案</category><category>犯罪企业</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>贩卖</category><category>走私</category><category>选举</category><category>国家的</category><category>总统选举</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Disney to Significantly Raise Prices of Disney+, Hulu Streaming Services]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Entertainment conglomerate also vows to crack down on password-sharing <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001115569"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="576" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831901?width=860&amp;height=576" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Disney Chairman and CEO Bob Iger is under pressure to address the company&#39;s streaming-business losses and deteriorating legacy TV operations.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: kena betancur/Agence France-Presse/Getty Images </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001115569"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/robbie-whelan" itemprop="url" rel="author">Robbie Whelan</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Updated Aug. 9, 2023 7:42 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/disney-raising-prices-hulu-espn-earnings-call-64ae262"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/DIS" class="">Disney</a> <span class="company-name-type">&#39;s</span> era of budget-priced streaming video packages and galloping subscriber growth has come to an end.</p><p> For the second time in about a year, Disney announced a round of major price increases to its streaming products, raising the cost of the ad-free versions of Disney+ and Hulu by more than 20% each. The company also vowed to <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/netflix-begins-charging-u-s-users-for-password-sharing-4bb7023e?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">crack down on password-sharing</a> , an effort that streaming rival <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NFLX" class="company-name">Netflix</a> started in earnest earlier this year.</p><p> The moves, along with deep cuts announced early this year, are geared toward achieving profitability for Disney&#39;s streaming segment by September 2024.</p><p> “Our streaming business is still actually very young,” Disney Chief Executive Bob Iger told investors during a conference call to discuss the company&#39;s latest results. “Because we&#39;re new at all of this,” he said, Disney still has to figure out how to properly balance pricing, cost savings and money spent on marketing.</p><p> The price increases and pledge to address account sharing come as the company earlier Wednesday said its streaming business lost far less money in the latest quarter <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/disney-dis-q2-earnings-report-2023-fcacec47?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">than it did in previous periods</a> , but reported that its flagship Disney+ streaming service lost domestic subscribers for the second quarter in a row.</p><p> The company also raised prices on its Hulu Live television packages and announced the launch of a new bundle known as the Duo Premium, which pairs Disney+ and Hulu without ads for $19.99 a month. Previously, the company had offered both services as stand-alone products, or bundled with ESPN+ for the same $19.99 price. The company plans to raise the price of the bundle including all three services to $24.99 a month. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="930" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/bdd2ef3a-5faa-48eb-9030-a6df0895ca6d-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> Wednesday&#39;s price increases, which take effect in October, mean that the monthly cost of the ad-free stand-alone version of Disney+ has doubled to $13.99 from its 2019 introductory price of $6.99. The price of Disney&#39;s ad-free Hulu service will rise to $17.99 from $14.99, making it more expensive than the most popular ad-free version of Netflix or <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/WBD" class="">Warner Bros. Discovery</a> <span class="company-name-type">&#39;s</span> Max streaming platform.</p><p> The cost of the ad-supported versions of Disney+ and Hulu won&#39;t change in the US, Iger said. “Maintaining access to our content for as broad an audience as possible is top of mind for us,” he said.</p><p> The changes come as Disney struggles to pivot from its old model of distributing content in movie theaters, on network and cable television and through the sale of physical media to a streaming-first paradigm.</p><p> Since launching Disney+ in late 2019, the company <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/disney-ceo-iger-need-to-figure-out-disney-pricing-strategy-aa470a0a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">has lost more than $10 billion</a> in its direct-to-consumer segment, which also includes Hulu and ESPN+. And for much of the past year, Disney&#39;s shares have traded below $100 as investors have grown impatient with media companies such as Disney that have spent heavily to acquire subscribers without giving priority to profit.</p><p> On Wednesday, the company reiterated its goal to have the streaming business break even by September of next year, a target Disney announced in late 2020, and said that a plan to restore its cash dividend, which was eliminated during the pandemic, by the end of 2023 was on track.</p><p> In March, Iger said that in its “zeal to grow global subs,” Disney had underpriced its streaming services and hinted that higher prices were coming. After the company in December launched its first-ever ad-supported tier for Disney+ and raised prices on the ad-free version by $3, the low level of cancellations indicated there was room to raise prices further without reducing demand, Iger said.</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> Earlier Wednesday, Disney reported that losses in its streaming business narrowed to $512 million in the third quarter from $1.06 billion in the year-earlier period.</p><p> The improvement is a sign that cost controls put in place by Iger are starting to show a positive effect: Wall Street analysts polled by FactSet had expected a quarterly loss of $758 million.</p><p> Overall, Disney&#39;s revenue rose 3.8% to $22.3 billion, thanks in part to continued growth at the company&#39;s parks business, while operating income remained flat at around $3.6 billion. Analysts surveyed by FactSet had projected revenue of $22.5 billion and operating income of $3.3 billion.</p><p> In a statement, Iger said Disney was on track to exceed the goal he laid out in February of <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/disney-dis-q1-earnings-report-2023-11675825320?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">cutting $5.5 billion</a> from content and administrative budgets, and chalked up the results to efforts to restructure the company and improve efficiencies. Since the start of the year, Disney <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/disney-to-start-its-7-000-job-cuts-this-week-6192d51e?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">has eliminated thousands of jobs</a> as part of an effort to reduce head count by 7,000.</p><p> On Wednesday, Iger said Disney&#39;s movie studios would be “not just reducing the number of titles we release, but also the cost per title.” </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/951a35f6-98af-492c-b4e6-58347328e6e3.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> Shares of Disney rose 2.7% in after-hours trading.</p><p> The company swung to a loss of $460 million from $1.41 billion a year earlier, mostly because of restructuring and impairment charges. Excluding certain items, Disney earned $1.03 per share outstanding, beating analyst expectations of 97 cents a share.</p><p> Disney+ had 146.1 million subscribers globally, 7.4% fewer than the 157.8 million it had in the previous quarter. The decline mostly came from India, where Disney last year lost the rights to stream <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/disney-wins-tv-rights-loses-streaming-rights-for-indian-premier-league-cricket-11655223683?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">a popular cricket league</a> that had been a major driver of new sign-ups.</p><p> In the US and Canada, Disney+ had 46 million subscribers, down from 46.3 million in the previous quarter. It marked the second time ever that the company saw Disney+ lose North American subscribers.</p><p> The company&#39;s parks business generated $8.33 billion in revenue, a 13% increase from a year earlier. The company said growth at its international parks offset lower results domestically.</p><p> Disney&#39;s troubled traditional television business <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/disneys-abc-espn-weakness-adds-pressure-to-make-streaming-profitable-196055c7?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">continued its decline</a> . The company&#39;s so-called linear TV segment, which includes sports network ESPN, ABC and cable channels like FX, Freeform and the Disney Channel, saw operating income fall 23% to $1.89 billion, or about $100 million less than what analysts expected. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831857?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Disney is exploring its options for ESPN and its other linear networks, including ABC and cable channels such as Freeform and Disney Channel.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Dylan Stewart/ZUMA Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Once a reliable engine of profit for Disney, linear TV has seen its operating income plunge in recent years as more consumers cut the cable cord and switch to streaming video as their primary source of home entertainment.</p><p> Iger recently hired Kevin Mayer and Tom Staggs, both former top lieutenants to Iger, as consultants to advise him on the TV business.</p><p> Disney <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/disneys-iger-hints-at-strategic-partner-for-espn-possible-sale-for-linear-tv-assets-35230a1a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">is exploring a menu of options</a> for both ESPN and its other linear networks, which include ABC and cable channels such as Freeform and Disney Channel, people familiar with the matter said. Those options could include selling some networks or bringing on equity partners, or spinning some assets off into a new company. News of Mayer&#39;s and Staggs&#39;s advisory roles was earlier reported in Puck&#39;s media newsletter.</p><p> In recent weeks, Iger has told associates that he wants to reduce Disney&#39;s exposure to the declining cable-TV industry but would prefer to avoid a spinoff of ESPN, and instead attract strategic partners to raise capital and ease the pressure on the business, people who have spoken with him said.</p><p> Separately, Iger <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/inside-disney-and-comcasts-fight-over-the-future-of-hulu-96a7aae6?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">is trying to take full control of Hulu</a> , the streaming service Disney owns in partnership with <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/CMCSA" class="">Comcast</a> <span class="company-name-type">.</span> A deadline that could force the sale of Comcast&#39;s one-third stake to Disney is approaching in a few months, and the two companies have already had on-and-off discussions. Battle lines are being drawn over the fairest way to calculate Hulu&#39;s value, setting the stage for a potential fight next year, people close to the discussions said. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=FB57A5A0-E270-46D2-B5D4-3ED0269F546E&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fdisney-raising-prices-hulu-espn-earnings-call-64ae262&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> This week&#39;s releases include the CPI inflation report, earnings reports from UPS and Disney. Data from the latest consumer credit report and quarterly household debt are also expected. WSJ&#39;s Dion Rabouin breaks it down.照片：乔·雷德尔/盖蒂图片社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>Kevin Lansberry, Disney&#39;s interim chief financial officer, said Wednesday that with $11.5 billion in cash on its balance sheet and $10.5 billion in debt instruments available, the company&#39;s war chest is well-stocked to get the deal done.</p><p> “We&#39;re very comfortable with our current liquidity position,” Lansberry said.</p><p> Iger also briefly addressed the continuing strikes by Hollywood writers and actors in Wednesday&#39;s call and in a memo to staff. After saying last month that the strikes were “very disturbing to me” and calling the unions&#39; demands unrealistic and disruptive, Iger softened his tone and noted that the strikes had prompted Disney to cut this fiscal year&#39;s spending on content from $30 billion to $27 billion.</p><p> “It is my fervent hope that we quickly find solutions to the issues that have kept us apart these past few months and I am personally committed to working to achieve this result,” he said.</p><p> Write to Robbie Whelan at <a href="mailto:robbie.whelan@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">robbie.whelan@wsj.com</a> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
